title: Mayer-Vietoris theorem
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

Suppose $$A,B \subseteq X$$ with $$\mathring{A} \cup \mathring{B} = X.$$ Then we have a long exact sequence (the Mayer-Vietoris sequence)
$$
\cdots \xrightarrow{\partial}
H_n(A \cap B) \to H_n(A) \oplus H_n(B) \to H_n(X) \xrightarrow{\partial} H_{n-1}(A \cap B) \to \cdots
$$